=== WikiHouse ===

[http://wikihouse.cc WikiHouse] is an open source construction set that enables anyone to design, download, print and assemble a house. Founded in collaboration with [http://www.architecture00.net/ Architecture 00], the WikiHouse project now has more than 10 chapters in cities around the world and a [http://www.ted.com/talks/alastair_parvin_architecture_for_the_people_by_the_people TED talk] with over a million views.



=== WikiFactory ===

We are developing [http://www.wikifactory.org WikiFactory] to enable design and hardware projects to collaborate as effectively as open source software projects. The in-browser, open source platform will feature a library of 3D designs and an easy-to-use design tool so that anyone can create, share and modify designs for digital fabrication.


=== Ampify ===

Set to launch in early 2015, [http://www.ampify.net Ampify] is an open source, decentralised application platform. It will provide a web-application framework to create social apps on top of a secure, decentralised core.

